review_blob: Beige lasting head. Heavily hopped traditional ale - spicy and crisp - grape like. Resin and fruit. long lingering taste. Lovely.
very nice sweet bock. very drinkable but tasty. bisquity, roasted, smokey - delightfull.
Average easter beer. Definately unfiltred! alright with typical danish easter lunch.

7,9% actually. New design looks better. Surpricingly drinkable for a very strong beer. Dobbelbock style with light yellow colour, white not lasting head. fine carbonation. Sweet, sirupy with little malt. Needs more hops but its there. Quite good for a discount supermarked beer
